- If the length of the string parameter `s1` is equal to 1, the boolean result is true.
- If the length of the string parameter `s1` is greater than 1, the string parameter `s1` is split into two non-empty substrings at a random index.
- The two substrings of the string parameter `s1` are randomly decided to be swapped or kept in the same order.
- The algorithm is applied recursively on each of the two substrings of the string parameter `s1`.
- The boolean result is true if the string parameter `s2` is a scrambled string of the string parameter `s1`, otherwise, the boolean result is false.